The paper deals with the decidability and complexity of determining equivalence of deterministic multitape automata, which is a problem in formal language theory (FL). The use of matrix algebras suggests a connection to data structures (DS) and algorithms. The randomised algorithm mentioned in the abstract involves matrix exponentiation, which is a topic in computational complexity (CC). The proof of decidability may involve group theory, which is a topic in logic (LO) and information theory (IT).
